  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Water and sanitation expert DRR-Team Mozambique 2020</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Water and sanitation expert for DRR-Team Mozambique.The embassy of the Netherlands in Maputo received 2 request for support of the DRR-Team.The request for DRR support in the city of Nacala, that suffers from erosion and floods, is to analyse the existing municipal report and to advise on measures (projects) to prevent erosion and improve drainage and to advice on financing options for the projects. A roadmap for next steps to further develop projects and to arrange finance will be included.The request for the city of Pemba focuses on the risk of floods due to abundant rainwater, floods from the sea during cyclones and sanitation. The DRR-Team is requested to review the existing report of Gauff Engineering (2015) and to analyse the erosion and flood situation, the underlying causes and to advise on technical interventions, governance and financing options to reduce the negative impacts of erosion and floods. The sewage system, WWT options and the localisation of the ETAR will be reviewed and advise is requested on conclusions regarding construction, treatment options and localisation of the ETAR. A roadmap for next steps to proceed to feasibility study and finance of the project, is to be delivered.The expert should be able to evaluate and design sewage networks, including pumping stations and wastewater treatment plants.</narrative>
  </description>
